Akanksha (@akkaul ) and her family came in as referral from one of Kevin's (@thebayarearealtor ) real estate colleague, Sanjog from AZ. It has been two years since our initial consultation. It's crazy how fast time flies!

I focused on the search in many areas and one thing Akansksha expressed was that she didn’t want to settle on a home. She stayed patient and until she found the perfect home,  we kept on touring.

Partnering with our skilled negotiator Ed (@ebarreto_25 ) he was readily available to show the property via FaceTime with Akanksha. Within 24 hours, she was convinced this unit was worth flying back into town for.

We went up against multiple offers and lost the first time, but the first buyer backed out due to work uncertainty. This was the ultimate chance to get the home she loved and that she did. It was a fast closing and we couldn’t be happier for her!

Amazing collaboration and team workout created the best experience for our client!

This client got an a OUTSTANDING deal! A duplex under one million is almost unheard of. 

They’re more expensive than that. Because they typically offer more space and amenities than a single-family home, they tend to be priced higher than comparable SFR homes in the same area.

The back unit can produce even more income with the garage when turned into an ADU. What’s an adu? 

Accessor dwelling units are living spaces that are attached to or located on the same property as a SFR. Often used as an additional source of income for homeowners, either through rentals or by providing a place for family members to live.

Are you looking for these types of opportunities? Dm/call/text me today!

"𝐈𝐭 𝐢𝐭 𝐚 𝐠𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐘𝐎𝐔 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐮𝐲? 𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭'𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧, 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐰𝐡𝐲 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐩𝐮𝐫𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚 𝐡𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐭𝐨𝐝𝐚𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐦𝐚𝐫𝐤𝐞𝐭?"

Buyers often ask me, "Is it a better time to buy now than it was a year ago? I say, buyers have more leverage than they used to. In the hottest market, even in the past two years. When I'm having these convesations with my clients, I'm telling them, "𝘙𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵 𝘯𝘰𝘸. 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘮𝘰𝘳𝘦 𝘭𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘨𝘦 𝘵𝘰 𝘯𝘦𝘨𝘰𝘵𝘪𝘢𝘵𝘦 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘱𝘳𝘪𝘤𝘦 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘮𝘴 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘥𝘪𝘥𝘯'𝘵 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘭𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘨𝘦 𝘢 𝘺𝘦𝘢𝘳 𝘢𝘨𝘰."

So when buyers ask me, is it a good time to buy? I'm always going to answer, "𝐈𝐬 𝐢𝐭 𝐚 𝐠𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐘𝐎𝐔 𝐭𝐨 𝐛𝐮𝐲?"

📢 Calling All First-time Homebuyers!

The Updated California State First Time Homebuyer Program is projected to be out by March 27th of this Year.  The State is going to give First Time Buyers a 20% down payment to purchase their First Home.  There is no payment or interest due on the 20% until the home is sold.  Once this happens the State will require the original 20% to be paid back plus 20% of the net appreciation.  Homeowner gets to keep the other 80% profit.

Feel free to connect with me if you are planning to buy your first home or anyone you know is a first time homebuyer who may be interested in this program. I would be more than happy to help :) 📩

Feel free to share this to your friends!

Throwback to when I got the opportunity to speak at our first Side REunite event in Napa. 

Nowadays, To succeed in the competitive environment, businesses just can't afford to miss out on the power of social media marketing. A lot has changed, and just posting about properties listed on the market, sold, pending, or in escrow just doesn’t make the cut. Engagement plays a big part, and being genuine and authentic with your audience is key. You have to put yourself out there, and let your name be known. You can mix it up a bit, and show them posts about family, friends when you’re on vacation, or just a typical day in a realtor’s life. Show them different facets of yourself and your audience, it’ll feel like you are working together with them.

#SocialMedia #SocialMediaMarketing #SidexSide #Realtorlife #Realtor #LetGGuideyou #GuilleanArradaza #GArradaza #GARealestate

“Give value. Give value. Give value, then ask for business” - Gary Veynerchuk

Most agents are afraid to ask for the business, believing that people think they’re just a salesperson and are only there for the business. But, I learned over the years that as long as you’re providing value, you won’t have that limiting belief that you’re just there to take someone’s business. I learned that I have more influence over my clients’ decisions than I give myself credit for. As an agent, we should leverage the influence we’ve built and the credibility and trust we’ve established to drive customers to a decision. Failing to ask for business means that all the time and energy spent building that relationship with the customer is left to chance. 

Be personable, be direct, believe, and know that you have your clients’ best interests prioritized. People are always looking to be helped. At the end of the day, you will always have what they need and that you are there to provide value as a business professional.

@insurance_gurl 🙌🏼

"ALMB"

Through our Zillow partnership we hit these metrics using this framework when we get inbound calls.

Truthfully, this can be used for all lead generations.

A - set the APPOINTMENT
L - Figuring out what LOCATIONS are of interest
M - What are the indicators of them buying and why are they MOTIVATED now.
B - Home run! Add multiple BONUS homes to your first meet with the client. Offer any potential off markets and coming soon homes as well.
